### Solution:

To find the difference, we need to compare the number of words Cam can type before and after he broke his arm for the same amount of time (e.g., 5 minutes).

Before breaking his arm, Cam could type 9 words per minute. So in 5 minutes:
9 words/minute * 5 minutes = 45 words

After breaking his arm, Cam could only type 6 words per minute with his left hand. So in 5 minutes:
6 words/minute * 5 minutes = 30 words

The difference between the number of words he could type before and after breaking his arm is:
45 words (before) - 30 words (after) = 15 words

So, Cam can type 15 more words in 5 minutes with his right arm than with his left hand.
